        <p>One way to measure and display data is to use a stem-and-leaf pl=
ot. A stem-and-leaf plot is used to visualize data. To set up a stem-and-le=
af plot we follow some simple steps.</p>
<p>First we have a set of data. This could for instance be the results from=
 a math test taken by a group of students at the Mathplanet School.</p>
<p><strong>13, 24, 22, 15, 33, 32, 12, 31, 26, 28, 14, 19, 20, 22, 31, 15</=
strong></p>
<p>We begin by finding the lowest and the greatest number in the data set. =
These are:</p>
<p>12 and 33</p>
<p>Then we draw a vertical line. On the left hand side of the line we write=
 the numbers that corresponds to the tens, 12 has 1 in the tens place and 3=
3 has 3 in the tens place.</p>
